"title": "6173: guilt, and God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6173",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>All human beings are guilty in the sight of God, and all require forgiveness and expiation of their sin. Guilt can arise through failing to know what is right, through failing to do what is right and through giving in to temptation to do wrong.</p>\n<h2>Guilt as the objective condition of sinners</h2>\n<h3>Guilt results from intentional sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:1-Lev6:7\">LEV 6:1–6:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:10\">JAS 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:5-Num5:7\">NUM 5:5–5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:14-Deut24:15\">DEU 24:14–24:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:13-Ezra9:15\">EZR 9:13–9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:1-Ezek22:4\">EZK 22:1–22:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:7-John16:8\">JHN 16:7–16:8</a></p>\n<h3>Guilt results from unintentional sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:13\">LEV 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:22\">LEV 4:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:27\">LEV 4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:17-Acts3:20\">ACT 3:17–3:20</a></p>\n<h3>Guilt as an accumulation of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:12\">HOS 13:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:6\">EZR 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:4\">ISA 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:20\">ISA 24:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's knowledge of human guilt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:5\">PSA 69:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:8-Gen4:10\">GEN 4:8–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:1-Josh7:26\">JOS 7:1–7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:22\">JER 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:4-1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h2>God's anger at human guilt</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:18\">2CH 24:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:10-Num32:13\">NUM 32:10–32:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:11-2Kgs22:13\">2KI 22:11–22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:13-Hos12:14\">HOS 12:13–12:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18\">ROM 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5-Rom2:8\">ROM 2:5–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6-Eph5:7\">EPH 5:6–5:7</a></p>\n<h2>God's determination to punish the guilty</h2>\n<h3>God himself punishes the guilty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:18\">NUM 14:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:5\">EXO 20:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:12\">JER 25:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:2-Nah1:3\">NAM 1:2–1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Human judges are to punish the guilty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:1-Deut25:3\">DEU 25:1–25:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:15\">PRO 17:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:23-Prov24:25\">PRO 24:23–24:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1-Rom13:5\">ROM 13:1–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a></p>",
